      <hedline>
        <hl1>THOMSON CHAIRMAN TO RETIRE</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Timothy Pritchard</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Pritchard, Timothy</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Kenneth Thomson says he will retire as chairman of Thomson Corp of Toronto within two years; family owns 73 percent of electronic publishing conglomerate (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Kenneth Thomson, ranked No. 15 on the Forbes magazine list of wealthy people, said he would retire within two years as chairman of the Thomson Corporation of Toronto. The Thomson family owns 73 percent of the company, an electronic publishing concern that accounts for most of the family's estimated wealth of $20 billion. Mr. Thomson, 76, has asked directors to name his son David, 42, as his successor.</p>
        <p>Timothy Pritchard (NYT)</p>
      </block>
